import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['departure_delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['departure_delay'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='departure_delay', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['departure_delay'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['departure_delay'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['flight_time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['flight_time'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data['flight_time'] = data['flight_time'].dt.hour + data['flight_time'].dt.minute/60
    avg_flight_time = data.groupby('airline')['flight_time'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='airline', y='flight_time', data=avg_flight_time)
    chart.axhline(avg_flight_time['flight_time'].mean(), color='red', label='Average flight time: {:.2f}'.format(avg_flight_time['flight_time'].mean()))
    chart.set(xlabel='Airline', ylabel='Average Flight Time (hours)')
    chart.legend()
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data['hour'] = data['time'].dt.hour
    data = data.groupby('hour').size().reset_index(name='count')
    sns.lineplot(x='hour', y='count', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the busiest time of day for flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Hour of the day')
    plt.ylabel('Number of flights')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = data['distance'].astype(float)
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='distance', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['distance'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['distance'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight distances?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
